        "username": "famoso",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/famoso/{size}/52759_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-06-30T02:08:26.881Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello,<br>\nI am writing on behalf of a more elderly person who I am in regular contact with, usually also over signal.</p>\n<p>She installed signal in ipad at a time where she wasn’t in possession of any mobile phone. Also the iPad did not have any sim card, at least not installed. That’s why we registered signal via the landline phone number. This worked fine and did not cause any issues for many years. Just until recently, around beginning of May.</p>\n<p>Around beginning of May, somewhere between 29th of April and 3rd of May 2025, signal all of a sudden showed the following behavior:<br>\nInstead of starting normally, it keeps asking to link signal to a mobile device. It does so by writing:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>(original text in German) Starte Signal auf deinem Mobiltelefon um dieses iPad mit deinem Konto zu koppeln</li>\n<li>(translation to english) Start Signal on your mobile phone to pair this iPad with your account</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It seems that Signal is assuming there would be another device with a full Signal installation set up, where iPad would join as an additionally linked device.<br>\nProblem here is, that this iPad is the one and only device ever being used with that signal account, which is why it’s not possible to follow Signal’s suggestions.</p>\n<p>Also I would like to mention: we wouldn’t mind setting Signal up on an iPhone, as meanwhile an iPhone is available. However, by doing so, I assume we would lose all message history, images and contacts. Especially, since the number would change, it would just be as if she was starting to use signal all over for the first time again. Also the loss of images etc would be sad.</p>\n<p>That’s why we have been hesitating since then, instead me trying to figure out a solution (and I have lot’s of other responsibilities, which is why we did not make any progress since beginning of May).</p>\n<p>I would formulate following questions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>why is it, that Signal all of a sudden asks to link to a mobile phone (especially since there never was such a mobile phone).</li>\n<li>are landline numbers no longer supported/ is it no longer possible to register with a landline number?</li>\n<li>why is it we aren’t even offered to re-register against a phone number at all, only being offered the option to link against a separate device?</li>\n<li>is there any way to transfer data, get backup etc? The Signal UI does not offer any option for that, as it basically only prompts for linking to a mobile device.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is the screen we are presented with:<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/4/74f8f04a5f46a01a3644cae482c3edf5f01479c1.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/74f8f04a5f46a01a3644cae482c3edf5f01479c1\" title=\"IMG_0219\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/4/74f8f04a5f46a01a3644cae482c3edf5f01479c1_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG_0219\" data-base62-sha1=\"gGMJzRPJVPpZnFMhxnCpiGqF9zb\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/4/74f8f04a5f46a01a3644cae482c3edf5f01479c1_2_375x500.jpeg, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/4/74f8f04a5f46a01a3644cae482c3edf5f01479c1_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/4/74f8f04a5f46a01a3644cae482c3edf5f01479c1_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"9097AC\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">IMG_0219</span><span class=\"informations\">1920×2560 150 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>Thanks upfront to anyone having an explanation, suggestion or whatever can help to clear up this situation!</p>\n<p>Best regards<br>\nFamoso</p>",
